cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CR

The paper proposes a novel approach to detect small objects in an image, specifically tiny faces. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with image processing, which is related to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also discusses the security implications of their approach, which makes cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible sub-category.
